        "title": "fix: guard setDeep against empty keys array in Chrome profile decoration",
        "body": "Related: #98465\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes `setDeep()` creating a property with empty-string key when `keys` is empty. Production callers (`decorateOpenClawProfile`) pass non-empty literal arrays.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdd early `if (keys.length === 0) return;` guard.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo user-visible change. Defensive guard.\n\n## Evidence\n\nRuntime verification (fix/empty-keys-setdeep, rebased on upstream/main 6495358f):\n\n```\nprofiles.test.ts — Test Files 1 passed, Tests 36 passed\n✓ profile name validation > accepts valid lowercase name: openclaw\n✓ port allocation > allocates within an explicit range\n✓ color allocation > allocates next unused color from palette\n... (36/36 ✓, Duration 5.19s)\n```\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard. `decorateOpenClawProfile` path exercised.",
